  "prompt": "How calculate aggregate?",
  "response": "To calculate an aggregate, you typically follow these steps:\n\n1. Simple Average Calculation:\n- Add all values together\n- Divide by total number of values\n- Formula: Aggregate = (Sum of Values) / (Total Number of Values)\n\nExample:\nValues: 10, 20, 30, 40\nAggregate = (10 + 20 + 30  40) / 4 = 25\n\n2. Weighted Aggregate:\n- Multiply each value by its weight\n- Sum weighted values\n- Divide by total weight\n\nExample:\nValue1: 10 (Weight: 0.3)\nValue2: 20 (Weight: 0.5)\nValue3: 30 (Weight: 0.2)\nAggregate = (10 * 0.3 + 20 * 0.5 + 30 * 0.2) / (0.3 + 0.5 + 0.2)\n\n3. SQL Aggregate Functions:\n- SUM()\n- AVG()\n- COUNT()\n- MAX()\n- MIN()\n\n4. Statistical Aggregation:\n- Mean\n- Median\n- Mode\n- Standard deviation\n\nChoose method based on specific context and requirements.",
